## geom_bar() just counts up the number of times
## social media levels appear in the data frame
ggplot(data = stat113_restructured, aes(x = SocialMedia)) +
  geom_bar()
## geom_col() allows us to specify the counts as an aesthetic
ggplot(data = stat113_restructured, aes(x = SocialMedia,
                                        y = n_social)) +
  geom_col()
